 For each of the following line equations, identify its slope. 



\begin{enumerate}[(a)]
\item \(-9 \, x - 3 \, y = 3\)
\item \(y = 6 \, x - 6\)
\end{enumerate}

     \end{exerciseStatement}
  \begin{exerciseAnswer} 

\begin{enumerate}[(a)]
\item \(-\frac{1}{3}\)
\item \(6\)
\end{enumerate}

     \end{exerciseAnswer}
 \end{exercise}

